<rationale>First, we find the position of the minute hand. The minute hand moves $6$ times faster than the hour hand, so it will be $\frac{1}{6}$th of the way around the clock from the current time. This means that after 15 minutes (which is half an hour), the minute hand will have moved halfway around the clock, which is $75^\circ$. Therefore, the smaller angle between the two hands is $15^\circ$, or $0.25\pi$ radians.</rationale>
